export let _markdown = "\n\n# Tutorials\n\nComprehensive step-by-step tutorials for analyzing 3D chromatin conformation data with Chr3D.\n\n## Tutorial Overview\n\n<Mermaid\n  chart={`flowchart TD\n  subgraph HiChIP[\"HiChIP Analysis\"]\n      HA[HiChIP API Tutorial]\n      HC[HiChIP CLI Tutorial]\n  end\n\n  subgraph HiC[\"Hi-C Analysis\"]\n      IA[Hi-C API Tutorial]\n      IC[Hi-C CLI Tutorial]\n  end\n\n  subgraph ChIAPET[\"ChIA-PET Analysis\"]\n      CA[ChIA-PET Tutorial]\n  end\n\n  FASTQ[FASTQ Files] --> HiChIP\n  FASTQ --> HiC\n  FASTQ --> ChIAPET\n\n  HiChIP --> LOOPS[Loops + Peaks]\n  HiC --> MATRIX[Contact Matrix]\n  ChIAPET --> LOOPS\n\n  style HiChIP fill:#e3f2fd\n  style HiC fill:#fff3e0\n  style ChIAPET fill:#fce4ec\n`}\n/>\n\n## Choose Your Tutorial\n\n### HiChIP Tutorials\n\nHiChIP (Hi-C + ChIP) captures protein-centric chromatin interactions with low input requirements.\n\n| Tutorial                            | Description                                                                                                            |\n| ----------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| [HiChIP API Tutorial](./hichip-api) | Complete Python API walkthrough with mermaid diagrams, ASCII logic explanations, class locations, and output structure |\n| [HiChIP CLI Tutorial](./hichip-cli) | Command-line interface guide with step-by-step execution                                                               |\n\n**Key Features:**\n\n* No linker filtering (HiChIP doesn't use linkers)\n* Restriction fragment-based purification\n* Distance-corrected loop calling\n* Peak calling from sPET\n\n### Hi-C Tutorials\n\nHi-C captures genome-wide chromatin architecture without protein enrichment.\n\n| Tutorial                       | Description                                                           |\n| ------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| [Hi-C API Tutorial](./hic-api) | Complete Python API walkthrough with pairtools and cooler integration |\n| [Hi-C CLI Tutorial](./hic-cli) | Command-line interface guide for contact matrix generation            |\n\n**Key Features:**\n\n* BWA-MEM alignment with Hi-C parameters\n* pairtools processing pipeline\n* Multi-resolution contact matrices (.mcool)\n* QC statistics generation\n\n## Quick Comparison\n\n| Feature           | HiChIP        | Hi-C           | ChIA-PET      |\n| ----------------- | ------------- | -------------- | ------------- |\n| Linker filtering  | No            | No             | Yes           |\n| Restriction sites | Yes           | No             | No            |\n| Peak calling      | Yes           | No             | Yes           |\n| Loop calling      | Built-in      | External tools | Built-in      |\n| Output            | Loops + Peaks | Contact matrix | Loops + Peaks |\n| Input cells       | \\~1M          | 1-10M          | \\~100M        |\n\n## What You'll Learn\n\nEach detailed tutorial covers:\n\n1. **Pipeline Overview** - Mermaid flowcharts showing the complete workflow\n2. **Source Code Locations** - Where each class is defined in the codebase\n3. **Output Directory Structure** - What files are generated and where\n4. **Step-by-Step Code** - Complete working examples\n5. **ASCII Diagrams** - Visual explanations of algorithms and logic\n6. **Expected Output** - Sample log output and statistics\n7. **File Formats** - Detailed format specifications\n8. **Troubleshooting** - Common issues and solutions\n\n## Getting Started\n\n### For HiChIP Analysis\n\n```bash\n# CLI approach\nchr3d run --mode hichip \\\n    --fastq-r1 sample_R1.fastq.gz \\\n    --fastq-r2 sample_R2.fastq.gz \\\n    --genome-index /ref/hg38.fa \\\n    --restriction-sites /ref/hg38_MboI_sites.bed \\\n    --output-dir ./output\n```\n\n```python\n# API approach\nfrom chr3d.mapping_v2 import PETMapper\nfrom chr3d.hichip_purifying import HiChIPPurifier\n# ... see full tutorial\n```\n\n### For Hi-C Analysis\n\n```bash\n# CLI approach\nchr3d run --mode hic \\\n    --fastq-r1 sample_R1.fastq.gz \\\n    --fastq-r2 sample_R2.fastq.gz \\\n    --genome-index /ref/hg38.fa \\\n    --chrom-sizes /ref/hg38.chrom.sizes \\\n    --output-dir ./output\n```\n\n```python\n# API approach\nfrom chr3d.bulk_hic import HiCPipeline\npipeline = HiCPipeline(...)\n# ... see full tutorial\n```\n\n## See Also\n\n* [CLI Reference](../cli) - Complete command-line documentation\n* [API Reference](../api) - Python API documentation\n* [Installation Guide](../getting-started) - Setup instructions\n";
